  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The first privacy-related concern lies in the mass-scale collection and storage of personal and sensitive data.",
    "With regards to collection, users are warned that their data may be shared with third parties in the consent form they sign to enter an agreement with, Amazon, or with any other data provider that is used to enhance AI polls.",
    "Though necessary, the privacy agreement has the unfortunate consequence of legitimising practices derived from the data of which users remain unaware, due to the density and inaccessibility of privacy policies.",
    "While giving the appearance of respecting deontic procedures, consent relies on the actual ignorance of users (Zuboff 2019).",
    "Against this view, it has been argued that consent to online privacy policies doesn't raise any particular moral concerns (Chomanski and Lauwaert 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Against this view, it has been argued that consent to online privacy policies doesn't raise any particular moral concerns (Chomanski and Lauwaert 2023)."
  ]
